1
00:00:04,690 --> 00:00:09,657
All of these things have to be understood
with great care and caution,

2
00:00:09,657 --> 00:00:12,598
according to Śrīla Guru Mahārāj.

3
00:00:12,604 --> 00:00:18,545
And I say this as someone who’s proceeded
incautiously thousands of times.

4
00:00:18,675 --> 00:00:22,941
[Ekadashi | Why Fast?]

5
00:00:23,043 --> 00:00:28,660
But it will always be the key,
the clue is devotion.

6
00:00:28,660 --> 00:00:29,914
Just as we sing 
 

7
00:00:29,914 --> 00:00:35,458
the śuddha-bhakata-caraṇa-reṇu
bhajana-anukūla.

8
00:00:35,660 --> 00:00:39,984
What’s favourable for devotion,
for devotion—

9
00:00:39,984 --> 00:00:45,001
that is favourable for you,
for me, for everyone.

10
00:00:46,448 --> 00:00:49,590
Not that what we think 
will be good, or …

11
00:00:49,590 --> 00:00:51,927
That’s why this song
is sung on Ekādaśī.

12
00:00:51,927 --> 00:00:55,995
мādhava-tithi, bhakti-jananī

13
00:00:55,995 --> 00:01:03,578
Mādhava-tithi means 
the different times or days

14
00:01:03,578 --> 00:01:05,888
that are dear to Kṛṣṇa

15
00:01:05,888 --> 00:01:07,935
(to Mādhava—
Mādhava means Kṛṣṇa).

16
00:01:07,935 --> 00:01:10,120
Mādhava-tithi, bhakti-jananī—

17
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:16,507
by honouring these days, such as 
Ekādaśī, Dvādaśī and other:

18
00:01:16,507 --> 00:01:20,407
Janmāṣṭamī, Gaura Pūrṇimā—
all these days …

19
00:01:20,594 --> 00:01:26,989
He’s saying it will be favourable
to the culture of devotion.

20
00:01:27,023 --> 00:01:31,154
Not that it will free you
from sinful activity …

21
00:01:31,159 --> 00:01:37,675
You did something wrong,
now you’re really in trouble, call mom …

22
00:01:39,990 --> 00:01:42,118
You’re in a jam.

23
00:01:42,699 --> 00:01:47,068
We need some karma-miśra-bhakti
to get us out of a jam.

24
00:01:47,664 --> 00:01:49,186
I’ve screwed up.

25
00:01:50,526 --> 00:01:52,106
Like those who’re saying
things like this,

26
00:01:52,106 --> 00:02:01,424
“Oh, I have blew it—on Ekādaśī,
I’ll fast on this day and recover from that.”

27
00:02:01,424 --> 00:02:05,221
What happens by imitating
Mahābhāgavatas?

28
00:02:05,221 --> 00:02:11,809
Like just Bhíma was given this benediction,
[from] who—from guru …

29
00:02:11,993 --> 00:02:14,971
He didn’t go like,
“Oh, well, let me think …”

30
00:02:15,671 --> 00:02:18,125
He asked his guru 
and he was told, “Yes”.

31
00:02:18,125 --> 00:02:21,670
He said, “I have this problem,
I can’t observe them …”

32
00:02:21,670 --> 00:02:27,295
“Alright, on this day if you’ll do this,
and for you, Bhíma,

33
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:30,720
it will be alright.”

34
00:02:32,262 --> 00:02:36,716
Not like this—“I am doing that,
me and Bhíma.”

35
00:02:42,282 --> 00:02:46,320
We are told, Śrīla Prabhupād cautions
in the Upadeśāmṛta purport,

36
00:02:46,320 --> 00:02:50,076
“You imitate Mahābhāgavata—
you go down.”

37
00:02:58,958 --> 00:03:04,440
So, what it takes …
following this idea, where did some go?

38
00:03:04,441 --> 00:03:09,387
They don’t follow or observe
any Ekādaśī during a year.

39
00:03:09,395 --> 00:03:13,830
Just once a year, this day, 
they don’t take any water.

40
00:03:14,128 --> 00:03:21,985
Is that bhajana-anukūla?
That’s favorable for devotion.

41
00:03:24,102 --> 00:03:27,187
It is to not understand this ...

42
00:03:27,187 --> 00:03:30,926
Dvādaśī is also bhajana-anukūla.

43
00:03:30,926 --> 00:03:34,901
What do you have to do
to observe Dvādaśī?

44
00:03:35,425 --> 00:03:39,465
Break the fast.
It’s very simple.

45
00:03:39,501 --> 00:03:44,073
In one place Guru Mahārāj said,
“More dear.”

46
00:03:46,523 --> 00:03:51,076
That can also be said …
And how do you observe that?

47
00:03:51,259 --> 00:03:55,708
By taking a little grain—what 
was forbidden the day before—

48
00:03:55,708 --> 00:04:00,291
you take one grain 
as pleasing to Kṛṣṇa.

49
00:04:01,487 --> 00:04:05,712
So what is the criterion—
is what is pleasing to Kṛṣṇa.

50
00:04:05,972 --> 00:04:09,576
Not, “I am trying to escape
the wrong I’ve done.”

51
00:04:09,576 --> 00:04:11,917
Like a bunch of karmis.

52
00:04:15,612 --> 00:04:22,224
Go to confession and confess,
“Bless me father for I have sinned.”

53
00:04:28,343 --> 00:04:34,469
Confess on Saturday,
 

54
00:04:35,448 --> 00:04:38,940
go to church on Sunday,
and start sinning on Monday.

55
00:04:38,940 --> 00:04:42,175
It’s good work,
if you can get it.

56
00:04:43,911 --> 00:04:46,507
Like mayi bhaktir hi … [Cc: 2.13.160]
what the Vraja-gopīs said?

57
00:04:46,507 --> 00:04:52,299
āhuś ca te nalina-nābha padāravindaṁ
yogeśvarair hṛdi vicintyam agādha-bodhaiḥ

58
00:04:52,299 --> 00:05:01,211
saṁsāra-kūpa-patitottaraṇāvalambaṁ
gehaṁ juṣām api manasy udiyāt sadā naḥ
[SB: 10.82.48]

59
00:05:01,211 --> 00:05:07,770
They told Kṛṣṇa, “We are not karmis,
we are not yogis, we are not jñānis,

60
00:05:07,969 --> 00:05:12,731
we are fallen householders—
saṁsāra-kūpa.

61
00:05:13,305 --> 00:05:15,677
Like the andha-kūpa—you hear
about it in the Scriptures—

62
00:05:15,677 --> 00:05:19,727
the blind well of household life.
That’s us.

63
00:05:21,703 --> 00:05:27,018
But even though 
that maybe who we are,

64
00:05:27,018 --> 00:05:32,945
still we can’t live 
without Your lotus feet.

65
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:42,750
So in such a self-denigrating, sweet and
affectionate way they present themselves.

66
00:05:42,780 --> 00:05:46,945
And they are worshipped
as the highest devotees.

67
00:05:50,423 --> 00:05:55,568
So Śrīla Guru Mahārāj said
quoting Saraswatī Ṭhākur—

68
00:05:55,568 --> 00:06:01,386
interestingly, he compared Ekādaśī,
Mahādvādaśī, other days to.

69
00:06:01,386 --> 00:06:05,438
He said, “First understand,
it is aprākṛta.”

70
00:06:07,002 --> 00:06:10,364
This is a very beautiful thing.

71
00:06:10,739 --> 00:06:16,371
Like we were saying before, 
it looks like it’s mundane, but it’s not.”

72
00:06:16,740 --> 00:06:21,543
So, how is it appeared to be?
He said, “From a mundane point of view,

73
00:06:21,543 --> 00:06:27,846
astrologically speaking, the Earth 
is under the influence of the Moon.

74
00:06:28,473 --> 00:06:32,650
Tides, also the flow of liquid;

75
00:06:32,750 --> 00:06:40,937
at a particular time of the month
the desire due to increased flow of rasā,

76
00:06:40,937 --> 00:06:44,040
the desire to enjoy is greater.

77
00:06:44,136 --> 00:06:48,090
So you need to make yourself dry.

78
00:06:48,538 --> 00:06:51,883
So fasting is recommended 
and also abstaining from foods

79
00:06:51,883 --> 00:07:01,375
that can agitate the senses 
or increase enjoying tendency.

80
00:07:01,375 --> 00:07:04,780
This is from 
an external point of view.

81
00:07:07,494 --> 00:07:12,233
And he pointed out also that
each one comes,

82
00:07:12,233 --> 00:07:19,070
the two times of month—the most intense,
full moon, and amāvāsyā, new moon—

83
00:07:19,070 --> 00:07:23,140
so few days before that
you make an adjustment.

84
00:07:23,595 --> 00:07:25,264
Pull back.

85
00:07:25,761 --> 00:07:28,809
But still this is external.

86
00:07:28,820 --> 00:07:34,750
But there aprākṛta, here is where
aprākṛta comes in.

87
00:07:35,511 --> 00:07:42,110
Kṛṣṇa—His desire at this time
is also greater.

88
00:07:42,930 --> 00:07:45,748
But what is His desire?

89
00:07:46,139 --> 00:07:52,615
When we say Kṛṣṇa’s desire, 
or the kāma of the Vraja-gopīs,

90
00:07:52,615 --> 00:07:55,777
this isn’t mundane desire.

91
00:07:56,000 --> 00:08:01,815
What’s pleasing to Kṛṣṇa 
is devotion.

92
00:08:02,112 --> 00:08:07,750
It’s inconceviable how the Vraja-gopīs
serve, but nontheless it’s devotion.

93
00:08:08,443 --> 00:08:17,220
ātmendriya-prīti-vāñchā—tāre bali ‘kāma’
kṛṣṇendriya-prīti-icchā dhare ‘prema’ nāma
[Cc: 1.4.165]

94
00:08:17,220 --> 00:08:25,291
What’s done to satisfy our own
notion of things and senses—

95
00:08:25,291 --> 00:08:26,948
that’s kāma.

96
00:08:26,958 --> 00:08:31,205
What’s done to satisfy Kṛṣṇa,
kṛṣṇendriya, Kṛṣṇa-indriya,

97
00:08:31,205 --> 00:08:35,136
the senses of Kṛṣṇa,
in Kṛṣṇa consideration—

98
00:08:35,136 --> 00:08:36,929
‘prema’ nāma, that’s prema.

99
00:08:36,929 --> 00:08:38,620
But they may look similar.

100
00:08:38,620 --> 00:08:41,182
Guru Mahārāj said, “They may look similar,
but they are different—

101
00:08:41,182 --> 00:08:45,986
North Pole, South Pole
in difference.”

102
00:08:47,928 --> 00:08:52,811
So what is really behind this,
why is it mādhava-tithi, bhakti-jananī,

103
00:08:52,938 --> 00:08:54,987
giving birth to devotion?

104
00:08:54,989 --> 00:09:00,429
Because at this time 
Kṛṣṇa’s desire is more;

105
00:09:00,441 --> 00:09:03,512
the higher devotees,
Guru Mahārāj said,

106
00:09:03,585 --> 00:09:08,728
they’re giving so much attention
to Kṛṣṇa at that time,

107
00:09:08,995 --> 00:09:14,612
they don’t have time to even think 
about eating, anything.

108
00:09:14,612 --> 00:09:18,547
They are not leaving 
His side for a moment.

109
00:09:18,547 --> 00:09:21,267
They are just serving Him.

110
00:09:21,372 --> 00:09:24,639
Can’t think about eating …
and forget everything …

111
00:09:24,667 --> 00:09:26,561
The higher devotees.

112
00:09:28,250 --> 00:09:31,038
And from this plane also 
the devotees are thinking,

113
00:09:31,038 --> 00:09:36,870
“Alright, so for these external reasons
we are going to fast this way and that way

114
00:09:36,984 --> 00:09:41,043
to check the mundane tendency.

115
00:09:41,328 --> 00:09:44,892
But, more importantly, 
we’re going to serve.”

116
00:09:45,067 --> 00:09:51,404
By a little bit of services this time,
it’s magnified.

117
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:59,472
It’s like, what do you call that—
exponentially.

118
00:10:03,214 --> 00:10:08,474
Little service draws greater
remuneration at that time.

119
00:10:09,281 --> 00:10:15,698
But the emphasis, like we told earlier,
will be on service.

120
00:10:17,550 --> 00:10:28,870
Not some trick; a trick I can do 
to achieve some devotional position.

121
00:10:28,880 --> 00:10:31,074
That would be mundane.

122
00:10:31,074 --> 00:10:35,587
That would be objective evolution,
not subjective evolution.

123
00:10:35,587 --> 00:10:40,856
That would be again manipulating 
the mundane to achieve the spiritual.

124
00:10:40,856 --> 00:10:46,313
That it’s not that by fasting 
you get devotion.

125
00:10:46,374 --> 00:10:51,651
But by, as Gurudev said,
by giving your energy to Kṛṣṇa.

126
00:10:54,262 --> 00:10:58,761
Once in Nabadwīp he said that, like,
“If you don’t feel something …”

127
00:10:58,761 --> 00:11:00,921
(there are different levels
we know of observing:

128
00:11:00,921 --> 00:11:04,746
no water, some water, 
some fruits,

129
00:11:04,746 --> 00:11:07,996
this, that, fast up to this time 
and then after that …—

130
00:11:07,996 --> 00:11:09,719
different ways.

131
00:11:09,896 --> 00:11:14,336
But Gurudev, the bottomline, he said,
“If you don’t feel something.”

132
00:11:14,336 --> 00:11:17,155
And we all, I think, we know
what that means.

133
00:11:17,155 --> 00:11:19,642
You feel a little …

134
00:11:20,462 --> 00:11:24,932
Mahananda Prabhu once said,
“Why is it like you could skip breakfast

135
00:11:24,932 --> 00:11:28,579
on any other day, but on Ekādaśī
you really feel it?”

136
00:11:28,627 --> 00:11:31,341
[Laughing]

137
00:11:31,341 --> 00:11:32,564
It’s true.

138
00:11:32,933 --> 00:11:37,470
Or you can tolerate your hair,
your fingernails, everything.

139
00:11:37,470 --> 00:11:42,477
On Ekādaśī your fingernails will drive
you crazy, and you want to cut them.

140
00:11:42,477 --> 00:11:45,620
Or get a haircut,
shave your hair.

141
00:11:45,620 --> 00:11:48,056
[Laughing]

142
00:11:48,056 --> 00:11:52,702
And we know this is true, 
by our practical experience.

143
00:11:53,993 --> 00:11:58,020
So Gurudev said, “If you don’t feel 
something on this fast …”

144
00:11:58,020 --> 00:11:59,490
And they’d say, 
“Well, how do I know when I …?”

145
00:11:59,490 --> 00:12:01,586
You’ve got to feel something!

146
00:12:01,586 --> 00:12:05,786
And Gurudev said, “In that way
something’s being offered to Kṛṣṇa.”

147
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:08,186
That’s what he said:
some of your energy,

148
00:12:08,186 --> 00:12:11,616
what you’re feeling, 
he equated it in that way—

149
00:12:11,616 --> 00:12:14,905
that’s what’s 
being given to Kṛṣṇa.

150
00:12:15,220 --> 00:12:17,803
So we are happy about that.

